{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1102].
  {panel}

It would be immensily useful to be able to sort issues in the order of urgency, in the same manner as releases are scheduled. This would make it really easy to see what is next on the list of things to do.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1076].
  {panel}

I would like to see a usefull feature:

Inc ase I want to "link" an issue to another issue, I would like to be able to browse through the existing issues in the "Link Existing Issue" window.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1072].
  {panel}

We need to share components among projects. This is a typical case,

There is a global project called "core assets" which provides reusable components for other projects.

Some components are created by the "core asset" team for the "X" project. So we would like to see the issues that are pending for the core team also in the X project.

In Admin if I select Statuses no statuses are displayed and there is no way to create one.
In the list of issues the status icon is not displayed (get default 'there should be a pic here' image), and the email that gets sent when an issue is created contains the following :

Status: ${config.statuses.getConstant($issue.getString("status")).name}
